  20     def modules_cleanup(oldmodules):
  21         # Encoders/decoders are registered permanently within the internal
  22         # codec cache. If we destroy the corresponding modules their
  23         # globals will be set to None which will trip up the cached functions.
  24         encodings = [(k, v) for k, v in sys.modules.items()
  25                      if k.startswith('encodings.')]
  26         sys.modules.clear()
  27         sys.modules.update(encodings)
  28         # XXX: This kind of problem can affect more than just encodings. In
  29         # particular extension modules (such as _ssl) don't cope with reloading
  30         # properly.  Really, test modules should be cleaning out the test
  31         # specific modules they know they added (ala test_runpy) rather than
  32         # relying on this function (as test_importhooks and test_pkg do
  33         # currently).  Implicitly imported *real* modules should be left alone
  34         # (see issue 10556).
  35         sys.modules.update(oldmodules)

  44 def create_package(file, path, is_package=True, contents=()):
  45     class Reader(ResourceReader):
  46         def get_resource_reader(self, package):
  47             return self
  48 
  49         def open_resource(self, path):
  50             self._path = path
  51             if isinstance(file, Exception):
  52                 raise file
  53             else:
  54                 return file
  55 
  56         def resource_path(self, path_):
  57             self._path = path_
  58             if isinstance(path, Exception):
  59                 raise path
  60             else:
  61                 return path
  62 
  63         def is_resource(self, path_):
  64             self._path = path_
  65             if isinstance(path, Exception):
  66                 raise path
  67             for entry in contents:
  68                 parts = entry.split('/')
  69                 if len(parts) == 1 and parts[0] == path_:
  70                     return True
  71             return False
  72 
  73         def contents(self):
  74             if isinstance(path, Exception):
  75                 raise path
  76             # There's no yield from in baseball, er, Python 2.
  77             for entry in contents:
  78                 yield entry
  79 
  80     name = 'testingpackage'
  81     # Unforunately importlib.util.module_from_spec() was not introduced until
  82     # Python 3.5.
  83     module = types.ModuleType(name)
  84     if ModuleSpec is None:
  85         # Python 2.
  86         module.__name__ = name
  87         module.__file__ = 'does-not-exist'
  88         if is_package:
  89             module.__path__ = []
  90     else:
  91         # Python 3.
  92         loader = Reader()
  93         spec = ModuleSpec(
  94             name, loader,
  95             origin='does-not-exist',
  96             is_package=is_package)
  97         module.__spec__ = spec
  98         module.__loader__ = loader
  99     return module

 102 class CommonTests(ABC):
 103 
 104     @abc.abstractmethod
 105     def execute(self, package, path):
 106         raise NotImplementedError
 107 
 108     def test_package_name(self):
 109         # Passing in the package name should succeed.
 110         self.execute(data01.__name__, 'utf-8.file')
 111 
 112     def test_package_object(self):
 113         # Passing in the package itself should succeed.
 114         self.execute(data01, 'utf-8.file')
 115 
 116     def test_string_path(self):
 117         # Passing in a string for the path should succeed.
 118         path = 'utf-8.file'
 119         self.execute(data01, path)
 120 
 121     @unittest.skipIf(sys.version_info < (3, 6), 'requires os.PathLike support')
 122     def test_pathlib_path(self):
 123         # Passing in a pathlib.PurePath object for the path should succeed.
 124         path = PurePath('utf-8.file')
 125         self.execute(data01, path)
 126 
 127     def test_absolute_path(self):
 128         # An absolute path is a ValueError.
 129         path = Path(__file__)
 130         full_path = path.parent/'utf-8.file'
 131         with self.assertRaises(ValueError):
 132             self.execute(data01, full_path)
 133 
 134     def test_relative_path(self):
 135         # A reative path is a ValueError.
 136         with self.assertRaises(ValueError):
 137             self.execute(data01, '../data01/utf-8.file')
 138 
 139     def test_importing_module_as_side_effect(self):
 140         # The anchor package can already be imported.
 141         del sys.modules[data01.__name__]
 142         self.execute(data01.__name__, 'utf-8.file')
 143 
 144     def test_non_package_by_name(self):
 145         # The anchor package cannot be a module.
 146         with self.assertRaises(TypeError):
 147             self.execute(__name__, 'utf-8.file')
 148 
 149     def test_non_package_by_package(self):
 150         # The anchor package cannot be a module.
 151         with self.assertRaises(TypeError):
 152             module = sys.modules['importlib_resources.tests.util']
 153             self.execute(module, 'utf-8.file')
 154 
 155     @unittest.skipIf(sys.version_info < (3,), 'No ResourceReader in Python 2')
 156     def test_resource_opener(self):
 157         bytes_data = io.BytesIO(b'Hello, world!')
 158         package = create_package(file=bytes_data, path=FileNotFoundError())
 159         self.execute(package, 'utf-8.file')
 160         self.assertEqual(package.__loader__._path, 'utf-8.file')
 161 
 162     @unittest.skipIf(sys.version_info < (3,), 'No ResourceReader in Python 2')
 163     def test_resource_path(self):
 164         bytes_data = io.BytesIO(b'Hello, world!')
 165         path = __file__
 166         package = create_package(file=bytes_data, path=path)
 167         self.execute(package, 'utf-8.file')
 168         self.assertEqual(package.__loader__._path, 'utf-8.file')
 169 
 170     def test_useless_loader(self):
 171         package = create_package(file=FileNotFoundError(),
 172                                  path=FileNotFoundError())
 173         with self.assertRaises(FileNotFoundError):
 174             self.execute(package, 'utf-8.file')

 177 class ZipSetupBase:
 178     ZIP_MODULE = None
 179 
 180     @classmethod
 181     def setUpClass(cls):
 182         data_path = Path(cls.ZIP_MODULE.__file__)
 183         data_dir = data_path.parent
 184         cls._zip_path = str(data_dir / 'ziptestdata.zip')
 185         sys.path.append(cls._zip_path)
 186         cls.data = importlib.import_module('ziptestdata')
 187 
 188     @classmethod
 189     def tearDownClass(cls):
 190         try:
 191             sys.path.remove(cls._zip_path)
 192         except ValueError:
 193             pass
 194 
 195         try:
 196             del sys.path_importer_cache[cls._zip_path]
 197             del sys.modules[cls.data.__name__]
 198         except KeyError:
 199             pass
 200 
 201         try:
 202             del cls.data
 203             del cls._zip_path
 204         except AttributeError:
 205             pass
 206 
 207     def setUp(self):
 208         modules = modules_setup()
 209         self.addCleanup(modules_cleanup, *modules)
 210 
 211 
 212 class ZipSetup(ZipSetupBase):
 213     ZIP_MODULE = zipdata01                          # type: ignore
